📈 Overall Progress
Day 104 was one of your strongest review days so far.

The biggest improvement wasn’t just remembering vocabulary—it was producing longer, more natural sentences with fewer pauses. Your weekly travel phrases now feel automatic, and you’re beginning to use conditional forms like le diría correctly after a little prompting.

You’re also making fewer word-for-word translations from English. Instead, you’re starting to recall complete Spanish expressions, which is exactly how conversational fluency develops.
